Vegetation is the most important component of the global terrestrial ecosystem. Influenced by human disturbance and climate change, global vegetation has shifted from a semi-wild terrestrial biosphere to a mostly anthropogenic biome (
 Ellis et al., 2010). The changes in the global vegetation or land use in the past were addressed in numerous studies (e.g.,  
 Wang, Price & Arora, 2006; 
 Li et al., 2017; 
 Song et al., 2018). However, few studies evaluated the individual contributions of human disturbance and climate change on vegetation changes, which is crucial to know whether the past vegetation changes are mainly caused by human or nature.
